                    <h3>Brockenhurst</h3>

                    <p>
                        Brockenhurst is a small village in the New Forest about mid-way between the towns of Lyndhurst
                        and Lymington
                        (and located on the main road between them).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        It is a truly lovely place, although very small, but the attraction is not the village so much
                        as it being
                        surrounded on all sides by the new forest. There is open forest dense with trees and paths
                        through them
                        (maintained pebble-covered paths as well as paths more correctly labelled "tracks") in some
                        directions, and
                        miles of moorland with spares growth and lots of grass in others.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can walk any one of dozens of routes in a circle and end up back at the village and there
                        are routes of
                        many times and near-infinite lengths.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        It is not only possible but quite easy and very pleasant to walk to Lyndhurst through the forest
                        by any of
                        multiple routes. You can walk through the forest on one side of the main road, and then walk
                        back through a
                        completely different forest on the other.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        There are two campsites just outside the village, one a smaller affair and one exteremely large
                        one



                        called Hollands Wood which is a "Camping In The Forest" campsite - a joint venture between and
                        Camping and
                        Caravanning Club and the Forestry Service.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Hollands Wood is <em>in</em> the open forest, meaning trees are everywhere, and so are the New
                        Forest
                        Ponies! There is no barrier around the campsite, it is litterally just in the forest, so the
                        ponies come and
                        go as they please. The site is massive and does not have marked pitches, you just pitch wherever
                        you want
                        (within certain rules). It can accomodate over 600 units.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Much as the ponies can wander around the campsite, they are also free to wander around the
                        village. It is
                        not uncommon to see them on the high street (see photos). The judicious use of cattle grids
                        keeps them from
                        certain areas - people's private property and the main road - but other than this is their turf
                        and humans
                        are just guests there.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Overall there's nowehere really like this place. Well, other villages in the New Forest I guess,
                        but I think
                        I meant the forest. It's truly beautiful, you could explore it for the rest of you life and
                        never run out of
                        new discoveries, the paths are very well maintained and are pleasure to walk onn, and it's
                        really easy to
                        camp there. Basically, it's Walker Nirvana.
                    </p>
